# Code Generation Rules (Flutter/Dart)

Code generation is a **first-class build dependency**, not an optional tool.

It must be:
- deterministic
- reproducible
- CI-verified
- never manually modified

---

# 1. Governed Code Generators

These generators are explicitly allowed and supported:

| Generator | Purpose |
|----------|--------|
| `freezed` | Immutable data models, unions, copyWith |
| `json_serializable` | JSON (de)serialization |
| `riverpod_generator` | Typed providers / state management |
| `go_router_builder` | Typed routing & navigation |

---

# 2. Core Rules (CRITICAL)

## MUST

- [ ] run `make gen` after any change to:
  - models
  - providers
  - routes
  - annotated classes (`@freezed`, `@riverpod`, etc.)
- [ ] treat generated code as build output, not source logic
- [ ] commit generated files to version control
- [ ] ensure CI always validates generated output consistency

---

## MUST NOT

- ❌ manually edit any generated file:
  - `*.g.dart`
  - `*.freezed.dart`
  - `*.gr.dart`
- ❌ rely on stale generated files during development
- ❌ bypass code generation step in feature completion

---

# 3. Build Pipeline Rules

## Required Commands

### Generate Code

```bash
make gen
```

- runs `build_runner`
- regenerates all annotated outputs
- resolves conflicts automatically (`--delete-conflicting-outputs` assumed via tooling)

---

### Verify Codegen Consistency

```bash
make gen-check
```

- ensures generated files match source state
- fails if uncommitted or outdated generated code exists
- must pass before any commit or PR

---

# 4. CI Enforcement

## Required CI Behavior

- [ ] code generation must be validated in CI
- [ ] stale generated files must fail build
- [ ] no untracked generated changes allowed in PRs

---

## Scripts (if present)

- `scripts/codegen_verify.sh` is authoritative check
- must be equivalent to local `make gen-check`

---

# 5. Dependency Awareness

Codegen correctness depends on:

- correct annotations
- correct `part` directives
- correct build.yaml configuration
- compatible generator versions

---

## MUST VERIFY

- `part '<file>.g.dart';` exists where required
- annotations match generator expectations
- no missing build.yaml configurations

---

# 6. Generated File Ownership Model

## Ownership Rule

- Source code = developer-owned
- Generated code = machine-owned

---

## Implication

- only source files are reviewed in PR logic discussions
- generated files are reviewed only for correctness/regression
- generated diffs are expected and required

---

# 7. Failure Modes (COMMON ISSUES)

## Stale Generation

Symptoms:
- runtime mismatch with model fields
- missing JSON fields
- broken routes or providers

Fix:
```bash
make gen
```

---

## Missing Parts / Imports

Symptoms:
- build_runner errors
- missing `.g.dart` references

Fix:
- verify `part` directives
- re-run `make gen`

---

## Conflicting Outputs

Symptoms:
- duplicate symbol errors

Fix:
- ensure `--delete-conflicting-outputs` behavior via tooling

---

# 8. Anti-Patterns (DO NOT DO)

## MUST NOT

- manually patch generated files
- commit without running `make gen`
- ignore build_runner failures
- disable codegen in CI
- partially regenerate files without verifying full build

---

